{
  "abstract": "In crosses between PI259747 (resistant to Puccinia arachidis) used as male parent on the one hand and NC17 and NC Ac2731 on the other, plants which had no nodules and which had yellow foliage were observed in the F2 from both crosses; the F3 from NC17 X PI259747 was also studied. The data from the F2 and F3 suggested that nodulation was controlled by independent duplicate genes and that it was plants with n1n1n2n2 which did not nodulate.\r\n\r\n",
